# Plan — Orschell Excavating E-Commerce Full-Stack

## Status: READY
All 5 research questions answered. Plan is finalized below.

---

## Demo concept

**"Orschell Supply Co."** — production-grade e-commerce platform matching Orschell Excavating's real brand (orschellx.com merch store) expanded with safety gear and site supplies. Full storefront + full admin CMS. Mock payment clearly labeled.

Slug: `orschell-excavating-e-commerce-full`

---

## Architecture

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Backend runtime | Node.js 22 + TypeScript + Express | Client's exact stack |
| Database | `node:sqlite` on Surface | `better-sqlite3` fails on Windows Node 22+ (gyp); Postgres-shaped schema; deck notes production target is PostgreSQL |
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite + TypeScript | Bundled to `public/demos/<slug>/`; source in `upwork-runs/<slug>/demo-src/` |
| API exposure | Flask bridge blueprint at `/demos/orschell-excavating-e-commerce-full/api/` | Standard Surface pattern |
| Auth | JWT (Bearer header), admin + customer roles, bcrypt hashes | Client requires auth system |
| Payment | Mock checkout — fake card form, success/decline simulation | Clearly labeled "Demo / Mock Payment" in UI |
| Clone source | `upwork-runs/adverteyes/backend/` (Express+TS+JWT structure); `adverteyes/demo-src/` (Vite+React pattern) | Direct structural reuse; swap `better-sqlite3` → `node:sqlite` |

---

## Feature scope (richness 10)

### Hero feature
**Full e-commerce storefront + admin CMS**

Customer-facing:
- Home: hero banner, featured products, category grid
- Shop: product catalog with category filter + search + pagination
- Product detail: specs, stock status, size/variant selector, add-to-cart
- Cart: drawer + cart page, quantity adjust, remove
- Checkout: shipping address + mock payment form (labeled), order confirmation page
- Account: login/register (JWT), profile, full order history with status badges

Admin CMS (role-gated `/admin`):
- Dashboard: revenue summary, order counts, low-stock alerts
- Product management: create/edit/delete (name, price, SKU, category, description, specs, image URL, featured flag, active toggle)
- Inventory: stock count edits, low-stock threshold per product, flag view
- Order management: all orders list, status pipeline (pending→processing→shipped→delivered), order detail

### Supporting features
1. **Inventory tracking**: stock decrements atomically on order placement; low-stock badges on product cards (storefront + admin)
2. **REST API with documented endpoints**: structured JSON, proper HTTP codes, admin-only guards — documented in proposal deck as the technical deliverable

### Explicitly out of scope (deck notes as production extensions)
- Stripe or real payment processor
- Email notifications
- Image file uploads (URL-based, seeded with realistic URLs)
- Shipping carrier integration
- Analytics beyond order/revenue counts

---

## Database schema (SQLite, PostgreSQL-compatible)

```sql
users         (id INTEGER PK, email TEXT UNIQUE, password_hash TEXT, name TEXT, role TEXT CHECK(role IN ('admin','customer')), created_at TEXT)
categories    (id INTEGER PK, name TEXT, slug TEXT UNIQUE, description TEXT, display_order INTEGER)
products      (id INTEGER PK, category_id INTEGER FK, name TEXT, slug TEXT UNIQUE, description TEXT, price REAL, sku TEXT UNIQUE, image_url TEXT, specs_json TEXT, featured INTEGER DEFAULT 0, active INTEGER DEFAULT 1, created_at TEXT)
inventory     (id INTEGER PK, product_id INTEGER UNIQUE FK, quantity INTEGER CHECK(quantity >= 0), low_stock_threshold INTEGER DEFAULT 5, updated_at TEXT)
cart_items    (id INTEGER PK, user_id INTEGER FK, product_id INTEGER FK, quantity INTEGER, UNIQUE(user_id, product_id))
orders        (id INTEGER PK, user_id INTEGER FK, status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending', subtotal REAL, tax REAL, total REAL, shipping_name TEXT, shipping_address_json TEXT, payment_ref TEXT, created_at TEXT)
order_items   (id INTEGER PK, order_id INTEGER FK, product_id INTEGER FK, quantity INTEGER, unit_price REAL)
```

Indexes: `products(category_id)`, `products(featured)`, `products(active)`, `inventory(product_id)`, `orders(user_id)`, `orders(status)`, `cart_items(user_id)`.

Inventory decrement: `UPDATE inventory SET quantity = quantity - ?, updated_at = ? WHERE product_id = ? AND quantity >= ?` — check rowsAffected = 0 for out-of-stock error (prevents oversell without transactions).

---

## REST API surface (20 endpoints)

```
POST   /auth/register              create account
POST   /auth/login                 JWT response
GET    /auth/me                    current user (auth required)

GET    /products                   list (category, search, page, limit, featured)
GET    /products/:slug             detail
GET    /categories                 all

GET    /cart                       user's cart (auth)
POST   /cart/items                 add item
PUT    /cart/items/:id             update qty
DELETE /cart/items/:id             remove
DELETE /cart                       clear cart

POST   /orders                     checkout (auth) — decrements inventory atomically
GET    /orders                     user's orders (auth)
GET    /orders/:id                 order detail (auth: owns or admin)

GET    /admin/stats                dashboard metrics (admin)
POST   /products                   create product (admin)
PUT    /products/:id               update product (admin)
DELETE /products/:id               soft delete (admin)
GET    /admin/inventory            all stock levels (admin)
PUT    /admin/inventory/:pid       update stock + threshold (admin)
GET    /admin/orders               all orders paginated + status filter (admin)
PUT    /admin/orders/:id/status    update order status (admin)
```

